FC Bayern will have to manage without Arturo Vidal. The Chilean picked up a knee injury in Sunday&rsquo;s training session. &ldquo;He slipped and went down,&rdquo; reported Jupp Heynckes on Monday at the pre-match press conference ahead of the DFB Cup semi-final at Bayer Leverkusen on Tuesday night (kick-off 20:45 CET).<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve just spoken to Dr. M&uuml;ller-Wohlfahrt on the phone. He&rsquo;s had an MRI scan. Arturo has a loose body in his knee. That&rsquo;s preventing him stretching. He&rsquo;s already on his way to Augsburg (to Dr. Ulrich Boenisch, Ed.). He needs keyhole surgery on his knee. Arturo will definitely be out of action for a while.&rdquo;

